I mean her house is filled with it because a boyfriend she had had abused her and they bought all this stuff together and blah blah blah.

00:39:33.807 --> 00:39:34.748
She had to get the law.

00:39:35.789 --> 00:39:38.312
It had to get the law out there, the law to say this is not your house.

00:39:38.853 --> 00:39:39.794
The boyfriend's got to go.

00:39:39.994 --> 00:39:41.516
You don't, you got to go.

00:39:42.036 --> 00:39:43.538
Friend, that's what you got to do with your sin.

00:39:43.714 --> 00:39:44.054
Okay?

00:39:44.255 --> 00:39:47.559
Hey, look, this is not your, my life is not yours.

00:39:47.839 --> 00:39:48.660
It is God's.

00:39:48.680 --> 00:39:50.883
He has redeemed it and I am His.

00:39:50.903 --> 00:39:51.884
You just got to reckon it.

00:39:52.004 --> 00:39:54.587
Whether you feel it or not, you got to reckon it down.

00:39:54.868 --> 00:39:55.008
Right?

00:39:55.028 --> 00:39:56.970
You got to put it in legally.

00:39:57.251 --> 00:39:58.953
You are His.

00:39:59.113 --> 00:39:59.954
Look at verse 18.

00:40:00.515 --> 00:40:04.640
Having been set free from sin have become slaves of righteousness.

00:40:05.301 --> 00:40:06.882
Frank, you will be a slave this morning.

00:40:07.804 --> 00:40:11.688
You will either be a slave to unrighteousness or you will be a slave to righteous.

00:40:11.768 --> 00:40:13.010
There is no middle ground.

00:40:13.506 --> 00:40:16.389
You will either serve unrighteousness or you will serve right.

00:40:16.409 --> 00:40:19.733
You will either serve the Lord or you will serve yourself and sin and Satan.

00:40:19.753 --> 00:40:21.175
There's just no two ways about it.

00:40:21.756 --> 00:40:23.518
You will be a slave to one or the other.

00:40:23.878 --> 00:40:25.720
The question is who slave are you going to be?

00:40:26.141 --> 00:40:29.124
Paul says, I am a slave to Christ Jesus.

00:40:29.605 --> 00:40:36.513
If you're going to break the chains of sin in your life, they've got to be replaced with the chains of love for him that redeemed you.

00:40:36.753 --> 00:40:39.216
How do you, it all has to do with how you pick your cross up.

00:40:39.756 --> 00:40:41.298
How did Christ go to the cross?

00:40:42.242 --> 00:40:45.847
Bible says, because of the joy that was set before him, he endured the cross.

00:40:46.528 --> 00:40:52.275
You pick up your cross and you die to yourself daily because of the love you have for him because he loved you first.

00:40:52.315 --> 00:40:53.597
Are you living that kind of Christian life?

00:40:53.697 --> 00:40:54.899
Can you live the pilgrim life?

00:40:55.179 --> 00:40:58.143
You can if you understand redemption and ownership and lordship.

00:40:58.183 --> 00:40:59.605
If not, you have no hope.

00:40:59.725 --> 00:41:00.726
Let's go to the Lord and prayer.

00:41:00.746 --> 00:41:07.135
Father, help us to put this deep in our hearts, deep in our minds, deep in our lives.

00:41:07.996 --> 00:41:09.458
When we leave this place,

00:41:10.146 --> 00:41:12.570
that we've been bought with a price that we are not our own.

00:41:14.613 --> 00:41:15.815
Oh, Father, help us be a people.

00:41:16.596 --> 00:41:28.895
When people see us, they don't just see our good works, but they see our good works and we glorify our Father in heaven because you have loved us and you have redeemed us by the precious blood of the Lamb.

00:41:29.095 --> 00:41:30.697
Help us understand this in Christ's name.

00:41:31.338 --> 00:41:31.719
Amen.

00:41:32.480 --> 00:41:39.090
If you'll stand with me, we're going to sing today in our hymnals in the time of prayer and reflection.

00:41:39.170 --> 00:41:40.672
number sixty eight.

00:41:41.393 --> 00:41:43.456
If you open your handles to number sixty eight.

00:42:05.309 --> 00:42:08.594
Thank you for listening to this sermon from Harvest Baptist Church.

